---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Daniel Tse and the editorial direction behind hack.danieltse.org.">
  <section class="page-lead">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Hands-on engineering leadership, written from the implementation layer.</h1>
    <p class="page-lead-summary">
      I care about the seam between architecture intent and production reality: AI systems that
      behave under pressure, backend services that stay understandable, and cloud platforms that
      reduce operational drag instead of multiplying it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="copy-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>What this site is for</h2>
      <p>
        This is the canonical home for my writing. Long-form essays live here first. Medium remains
        useful for distribution and discovery, but the durable version belongs on a site I control.
      </p>
      <p>
        The editorial line is deliberate: practical systems thinking, implementation detail, and
        tradeoff-heavy engineering rather than generic trend commentary.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>What I write about</h2>
      <p>
        Expect essays on local LLMs, integration protocols, JVM and Kotlin backend work, cloud
        infrastructure, delivery pipelines, and the kind of operational details that decide whether
        an architecture is elegant only on slides or robust in production.
      </p>
      <p>
        Notes will be shorter and more tactical. Essays are where I expand the reasoning.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

